ADR-007: Graceful Degradation and Disaster Recovery

NoUI Platform Architecture Decision Record

**Date:** February 19, 2026

**Status:** Accepted

**Deciders:** Jeff (Technical Director)

Context

The NoUI platform must continue serving pension agency staff even when
components fail. Staff cannot be left unable to process member
transactions due to AI service outages, network issues, or
infrastructure failures. This ADR establishes a six-level degradation
hierarchy that maintains core functionality under all failure
conditions.

Decision

Implement a six-level degradation hierarchy from Level 0 (Normal
Operations) through Level 5 (Complete Outage). Each level defines
specific trigger conditions, system behaviors, and staff-visible
indicators. The system automatically transitions between levels based on
component health checks.

Degradation Levels

Level 0: Normal Operations

**Trigger:** All services healthy

**Behavior:** Full AI-assisted workspace composition, intelligent
prioritization, proactive suggestions

**Staff Indicator:** Green status indicator, no degradation notice

Level 1: AI Composition Degraded

**Trigger:** Claude API latency \> 2 seconds or error rate \> 5%

**Behavior:** Fall back to rule-based (Tier 1 + Tier 2) workspace
composition. No AI-suggested layouts. Cached AI insights still displayed
if recent.

**Staff Indicator:** Yellow indicator: \'AI assistance temporarily
limited\'

Level 2: AI Services Unavailable

**Trigger:** Claude API completely unreachable for \> 30 seconds

**Behavior:** All AI features disabled. Static workspaces only
(pre-configured per process type). Rules engine continues operating
normally. All calculations accurate.

**Staff Indicator:** Orange indicator: \'AI services offline - using
standard workspaces\'

Level 3: Intelligence Services Degraded

**Trigger:** Internal intelligence services (relevance engine,
orchestrator) degraded

**Behavior:** No intelligent prioritization. All data shown in default
order. Rules engine continues. Calculations accurate.

**Staff Indicator:** Orange indicator: \'Limited functionality - core
calculations available\'

Level 4: Data Connector Read-Only

**Trigger:** Legacy database write failures or transaction timeouts

**Behavior:** Read-only mode. Staff can view member data and calculate
benefits but cannot save transactions. Offline queue for pending
transactions.

**Staff Indicator:** Red indicator: \'READ ONLY - Transactions will be
queued\'

Level 5: Complete Outage

**Trigger:** Legacy database completely unreachable

**Behavior:** System unavailable. Static maintenance page displayed.
Automatic recovery attempts every 30 seconds.

**Staff Indicator:** Red full-screen: \'System temporarily unavailable -
IT has been notified\'

Key Principle

**The rules engine and benefit calculations never degrade.** At every
level from 0 through 4, if a member record can be retrieved, the benefit
calculation will be accurate. AI features degrade gracefully; fiduciary
calculations do not.

POC Implementation Requirements

For the DERP POC, implement:

1\. Health check endpoints for all services with configurable thresholds

2\. Static fallback workspaces for service retirement process

3\. Visual degradation indicators in the workspace header

4\. Orchestration state persistence for recovery

5\. Demonstration mode to simulate each degradation level

Consequences

**Positive:** Staff can always process critical transactions. Agency
confidence in system reliability. Clear communication of system status.

**Negative:** Additional complexity in service design. Static fallback
workspaces require maintenance. Testing matrix increases.
